    {
      "text": "A 19-year-old female college student reports pain, swelling, and bruising of the ulnar aspect of the right hand after punching a heavy bag at the gym.\nThe skin on her hand is intact; severe edema and ecchymosis are most prominent over the dorsal aspect of the fourth and fifth metacarpals. The small finger is visibly shortened; however, there is symmetric finger flexion to the palm compared with the uninjured hand. The patient is exquisitely tender to palpation over the dorsal fifth metacarpal. Pain limits her range of motion. Axial loading of the ring finger exacerbates the pain. Her distal neurovascular status is intact.\nA radiograph of the right hand is obtained (figure).\nIn addition to rest, ice, and use of a nonsteroidal antiinflammatory drug, which one of the following next steps is most appropriate for this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Application of a cast"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Closed reduction"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Digital block for pain control and discharge to home"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Referral for open exploration"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Application of a splint"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>A <span data-sememe-id=\"3hVSd80\">splint</span> and cast are appropriate after (but not before) <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"EVb8ws\">closed reduction</a> in this case.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) CORRECT:</h4>Boxer’s <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fractures</a> are common orthopedic injuries managed in outpatient settings. They usually involve the neck of the fifth <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3p0S6S&anker=Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-learningcard-id=\"3p0S6S\" data-anker=\"Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-section-id=\"swct4e0\" data-sememe-id=\"fYXko9\">metacarpal</a>. It is best to begin with <span data-sememe-id=\"cdbaKs\">conservative measures</span>, including ice application, elevation, and oral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> medication. Some studies report acceptable functional outcomes in patients with up to 70 degrees of <span data-sememe-id=\"3j0SZT\">volar</span> angulation. However, to ensure the best chance of recovery with limited range-of-motion deficits, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"EVb8ws\">closed reduction</a> is recommended when <span data-sememe-id=\"3j0SZT\">volar</span> angulation is greater than 40 to 50 degrees, as in this case.<br><br>A <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z02cbf02e95d7b84aac89b0eb532c01cd\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z02cbf02e95d7b84aac89b0eb532c01cd\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"zCaru5\">hematoma</a> or ulnar block provides good <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dt0oc3&anker=Z4bb46e589405b756819918089790d4ee\" data-learningcard-id=\"dt0oc3\" data-anker=\"Z4bb46e589405b756819918089790d4ee\" data-sememe-id=\"HUdKe60\">local anesthesia</a> before attempting the reduction. With the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3p0S6S&anker=Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-learningcard-id=\"3p0S6S\" data-anker=\"Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-section-id=\"swct4e0\" data-sememe-id=\"fYXko9\">metacarpal</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Bo0zVS&anker=Z42dfc5649a4025fa49ffc6ebd8712c18\" data-learningcard-id=\"Bo0zVS\" data-anker=\"Z42dfc5649a4025fa49ffc6ebd8712c18\">joint</a> at 90 degrees, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z1d32c337522f0bca8f95a079c33fb2b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z1d32c337522f0bca8f95a079c33fb2b1\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"xjdEcJ0\">traction</a> should be applied in concert with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z8a41e7a525b2475efb31151d047328ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z8a41e7a525b2475efb31151d047328ba\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">dorsal</a> pressure to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> site. After reduction is achieved, a plaster ulnar-gutter safety <span data-sememe-id=\"3hVSd80\">splint</span> should be applied, followed by postreduction radiographs to ensure adequate reduction and alignment. A follow-up appointment for cast application and repeat radiographs is the next step.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> In addition to rest, ice, and use of an antiinflammatory drug, the most appropriate management for a patient with boxer’s <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> involving the fifth <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3p0S6S&anker=Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-learningcard-id=\"3p0S6S\" data-anker=\"Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-section-id=\"swct4e0\" data-sememe-id=\"fYXko9\">metacarpal</a> neck with 60 degrees of <span data-sememe-id=\"3j0SZT\">volar</span> angulation is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"EVb8ws\">closed reduction</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>A <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sl0ywT&anker=Z5c7ae52983033df636463099792e7cb8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sl0ywT\" data-anker=\"Z5c7ae52983033df636463099792e7cb8\" data-section-id=\"pNcLX10\" data-sememe-id=\"ASaRX4\">digital block</a> is useful for providing anesthesia when managing isolated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=N30-if&anker=Z205e38c58acd4e75816fc3df4cb7f2d8\" data-learningcard-id=\"N30-if\" data-anker=\"Z205e38c58acd4e75816fc3df4cb7f2d8\">finger injuries</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">Pain</a> related to a boxer’s <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> is unlikely to respond to a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sl0ywT&anker=Z5c7ae52983033df636463099792e7cb8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sl0ywT\" data-anker=\"Z5c7ae52983033df636463099792e7cb8\" data-section-id=\"pNcLX10\" data-sememe-id=\"ASaRX4\">digital block</a>, given its relative <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z3538c7d0d3c09a64652ecccc7971d5ae\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z3538c7d0d3c09a64652ecccc7971d5ae\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">proximal</a> location; this patient’s <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> requires immediate management.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Orthopedic consultation with possible open exploration is required for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z708eb53730eab4e281775dc19bb84379\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z708eb53730eab4e281775dc19bb84379\" data-section-id=\"2HWTp50\" data-sememe-id=\"f1bkTs\">open fractures</a>, neurovascular compromise, rotation, and failed reduction. This case is not complicated by any of those factors.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>A <span data-sememe-id=\"3hVSd80\">splint</span> and cast are appropriate after (but not before) <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"EVb8ws\">closed reduction</a> in this case.</div>",
