      "text": "A 19-year-old female college student reports pain, swelling, and bruising of the ulnar aspect of the right hand after punching a heavy bag at the gym. The skin on her hand is intact; severe edema and ecchymosis are most prominent over the dorsal aspect of the fourth and fifth metacarpals. The small finger is visibly shortened; however, there is symmetric finger flexion to the palm compared with the uninjured hand. The patient is exquisitely tender to palpation over the dorsal fifth metacarpal. Axial loading of the ring finger exacerbates the pain. An x-ray of the right hand is shown. In addition to rest, ice, and use of a nonsteroidal antiinflammatory drug, which of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?",
