      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Applying a cast is appropriate after performing another clinical intervention; however, it is not the most appropriate next step in management.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) CORRECT:</h4>Boxer’s <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fractures</a> are common orthopedic injuries managed in outpatient settings. They usually involve the neck of the fifth <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3p0S6S&anker=Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-learningcard-id=\"3p0S6S\" data-anker=\"Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-section-id=\"swct4e0\" data-sememe-id=\"fYXko9\">metacarpal</a>. It is best to begin with <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><span data-sememe-id=\"cdbaKs\">conservative measures</span></b></span>, including ice application, elevation, and oral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> medication. Some studies report acceptable functional outcomes in patients with up to 70 degrees of <span data-sememe-id=\"3j0SZT\">volar</span> angulation. However, to ensure the best chance of recovery with limited range-of-motion deficits, <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"EVb8ws\">closed reduction</a> is recommended </b></span>when <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><span data-sememe-id=\"3j0SZT\">volar</span> angulation is greater than 40 to 50 degrees</b></span>, as in this case.<br><br>A <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z02cbf02e95d7b84aac89b0eb532c01cd\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z02cbf02e95d7b84aac89b0eb532c01cd\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"zCaru5\">hematoma</a> or ulnar block provides good <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dt0oc3&anker=Z4bb46e589405b756819918089790d4ee\" data-learningcard-id=\"dt0oc3\" data-anker=\"Z4bb46e589405b756819918089790d4ee\" data-sememe-id=\"HUdKe60\">local anesthesia</a> before attempting the reduction. With the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3p0S6S&anker=Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-learningcard-id=\"3p0S6S\" data-anker=\"Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-section-id=\"swct4e0\" data-sememe-id=\"fYXko9\">metacarpal</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Bo0zVS&anker=Z42dfc5649a4025fa49ffc6ebd8712c18\" data-learningcard-id=\"Bo0zVS\" data-anker=\"Z42dfc5649a4025fa49ffc6ebd8712c18\">joint</a> at 90 degrees, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z1d32c337522f0bca8f95a079c33fb2b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z1d32c337522f0bca8f95a079c33fb2b1\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"xjdEcJ0\">traction</a> should be applied in concert with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z8a41e7a525b2475efb31151d047328ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z8a41e7a525b2475efb31151d047328ba\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">dorsal</a> pressure to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> site. After reduction is achieved, a plaster ulnar-gutter safety <span data-sememe-id=\"3hVSd80\">splint</span> should be applied, followed by postreduction radiographs to ensure adequate reduction and alignment. A follow-up appointment for cast application and repeat radiographs is the next step.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> In addition to rest, ice, and use of an antiinflammatory drug, the most appropriate management for a patient with boxer’s <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> involving the fifth <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3p0S6S&anker=Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-learningcard-id=\"3p0S6S\" data-anker=\"Z27a865e4ece090e62885a6bec2d2848f\" data-section-id=\"swct4e0\" data-sememe-id=\"fYXko9\">metacarpal</a> neck with 60 degrees of <span data-sememe-id=\"3j0SZT\">volar</span> angulation is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z49b338752aa93adc1559de60e295dbd9\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"EVb8ws\">closed reduction</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_55590ee17df46.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>X-ray right hand (oblique view)</p><p>An acute oblique fracture of the fifth metacarpal neck is accompanied by volar and radial angulation of the distal fragment. Sometimes termed a “boxer's fracture,” this injury is frequently the result of a closed fist colliding with a solid surface at high speeds.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>A <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sl0ywT&anker=Z5c7ae52983033df636463099792e7cb8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sl0ywT\" data-anker=\"Z5c7ae52983033df636463099792e7cb8\" data-section-id=\"pNcLX10\" data-sememe-id=\"ASaRX4\">digital block</a> is useful for providing anesthesia when managing isolated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=N30-if&anker=Z205e38c58acd4e75816fc3df4cb7f2d8\" data-learningcard-id=\"N30-if\" data-anker=\"Z205e38c58acd4e75816fc3df4cb7f2d8\">finger injuries</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">Pain</a> related to a boxer’s <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> is unlikely to respond to a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sl0ywT&anker=Z5c7ae52983033df636463099792e7cb8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sl0ywT\" data-anker=\"Z5c7ae52983033df636463099792e7cb8\" data-section-id=\"pNcLX10\" data-sememe-id=\"ASaRX4\">digital block</a>, given its relative <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z3538c7d0d3c09a64652ecccc7971d5ae\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z3538c7d0d3c09a64652ecccc7971d5ae\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">proximal</a> location; this patient’s <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> requires immediate management.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Orthopedic consultation with possible open exploration is required for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z708eb53730eab4e281775dc19bb84379\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z708eb53730eab4e281775dc19bb84379\" data-section-id=\"2HWTp50\" data-sememe-id=\"f1bkTs\">open fractures</a>, neurovascular compromise, rotation, and failed reduction. This case is not complicated by any of those factors.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Applying a <span data-sememe-id=\"3hVSd80\">splint</span> is appropriate after performing another clinical intervention; however, it is not the most appropriate next step in management.</div>",
